COLLABORATOR","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"## Pain Point\r\n\r\nCurrently almost all models use a if else block to determine which location to use, the one provided by the config or the temp dir\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/intel/dffml/blob/e7a356dfe8fd6fdf3cac7f8c218abc7d650fd93c/model/tensorflow/dffml_model_tensorflow/tf_base.py#L136-L146\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/intel/dffml/blob/e7a356dfe8fd6fdf3cac7f8c218abc7d650fd93c/model/pytorch/dffml_model_pytorch/pytorch_base.py#L364-L374\r\n\r\n## Proposed Solution\r\n\r\nAdd a `@property` on `Model` Base-Class to fetch this at one place \r\n\r\n```py\r\n@property \r\n def location(self): \r\n     return ( \r\n         self.config.location \r\n         if not hasattr(self, \"temp_dir\") \r\n         else self.temp_dir \r\n     ) \r\n```","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/intel/dffml/issues/1260/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/intel/dffml/issues/1260/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}